@page "/help"
@layout Layout.EmptyLayout

<MudPaper Class="ma-1 pa-4" Elevation="0">    
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" GutterBottom="true">@localizer.Html("_HelpPageMessage")</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" GutterBottom="true">
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">1. What is OVMC?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    OVMC (Oman Visa and Medical Center) is the visa and medical center where foreign worker candidates complete biometrics and a pre-arrival medical check before travelling to Oman.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">2. Who needs to follow this OVMC process?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    This process is for all foreign workers applying for a worker visa for Oman, coming from a source country which requires medical clearance before working in Oman.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">3. Why is OVMC required for Filipino workers?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    All expatriate workers from the Philippines must complete OVMC processing, including biometrics and the pre-arrival medical check in Manila, before arriving in Oman.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">4. What is the process in one quick summary?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Get MOL work permit (via Sanad) → Register/Login on OVMC portal → Add candidate details → Pay online and get URN → Book appointment via VFS Global → Candidate completes biometrics + medical at OVMC Manila → Fitness certificate is issued → Continue remaining formalities in Oman.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">5. What do I need before I start on the OVMC portal?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    You must already have the approved MOL work permit obtained through the Ministry of Labour.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">6. Which website do I apply from?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    The website is www.ovmc.omanpost.om
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">7. Do I need to register on the portal every time?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    No. Sponsor registration is a one-time step. After that, you can log in and create requests for candidates.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">8. What details are needed to register as a sponsor?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    You’ll need your sponsor name, CR/National ID, sponsor type and city, phone number registered with MOL, email address, password, OTP verification, and acceptance of Terms & Conditions.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">9. What do I use as my username to log in?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Your sponsor phone number is your username.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">10. I’m not receiving the OTP. What should I check?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Make sure the phone number matches the number registered with MOL.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">11. What does “initiate an OVMC request” mean?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    It means creating a new request in the portal for a candidate before payment and appointment booking.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">12. What candidate details do I need to enter?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    MOL work permit number, country and city, visa type, passport details, applicant name, date of birth, gender, marital status, email, and phone number.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">13. Can I review the candidate information before paying?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Yes. You can review and edit the form before proceeding to payment.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">14. Until when can I edit the candidate’s details?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Applicant demographic details can be edited until the appointment process starts at OVMC.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">15. Why do passport details need extra attention?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Passport details must exactly match the passport to avoid delays.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">16. What happens after I pay online?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    The system generates a Unique Reference Number (URN) and payment receipt.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">17. What is a URN?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    URN stands for Unique Reference Number used for appointment booking and follow-ups.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">18. What should I keep after payment?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Keep both the URN and payment receipt for booking and follow-ups.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">19. Are the OVMC processing fees refundable or transferable?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    No. OVMC processing fees are non-refundable and non-transferable.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">20. Where can I see my submitted candidate details later?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    All submitted candidate details appear in the portal’s History tab.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">21. When do I start appointment booking?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    After the URN is generated.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">22. What happens when I click to book the appointment?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    You are redirected to the OVMC VFS Global website to schedule the appointment.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">23. Who can book the appointment on VFS?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    The sponsor, recruitment agent, or candidate can book the appointment using the URN and passport number.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">24. What do I need to book the appointment?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    The URN and the candidate’s passport number.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">25. During booking, which candidate details can I change?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Personal details are non-editable, but contact information can be updated.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">26. How do I choose the appointment slot?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Select the preferred OVMC center and appointment date on the scheduling screen.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">27. Is there a final check before confirming the appointment?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Yes. Applicant details are reviewed again on the Order Summary page.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">28. What do I get after the appointment is booked successfully?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    An appointment letter is generated.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">29. What should the candidate bring to OVMC Manila?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    The appointment letter and original passport.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">30. What happens at OVMC Manila, and what’s next?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Biometrics and medical tests are completed. A medical fitness certificate is issued by email, and the candidate can continue the remaining formalities in Oman.
                </div>
            </div>

   
    </MudText>
</MudPaper>

<style>
    body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin: 40px;
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
        color: #333;
    }


    h1 {
        text-align: center;
        color: #004080;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    .faq-item {
        margin-bottom: 25px;
        padding-bottom: 15px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
    }

    .faq-question {
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #004080;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .faq-answer {
        margin-left: 10px;
    }
</style>